# Ekya — E2EE Real-Time Collaborative CRDT Framework

An SDK/framework for building real-time collaborative applications (text editors, whiteboards, shared state) where the **central server never sees plaintext data**. CRDTs handle conflict-free merging; E2EE ensures the relay server is completely trustless.

## Background & Design Philosophy

Building on:
- **SecureConnect** — E2EE messaging with RSA-OAEP + AES-GCM, Web Crypto API, Socket.IO, WebRTC
- **Kalpa** — meta-protocol router with UME, backpressure, hot-swap (potential future integration as the signaling backbone)

**Core insight**: CRDTs produce deterministic merge results regardless of operation order. This means we can encrypt each operation *independently* — the server relays opaque ciphertext blobs, and clients decrypt + merge locally.

### Architecture Overview

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                   Client (Browser)                   │
│                                                     │
│  ┌─────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────────────┐  │
│  │  CRDT   │──▶│  Crypto  │──▶│   Net (WS/RTC)   │  │
│  │ Engine  │◀──│  Layer   │◀──│   Transport      │  │
│  └─────────┘   └──────────┘   └────────┬─────────┘  │
│       │                                │             │
│  ┌────▼────┐                           │             │
│  │EkyaDoc  │  (Developer API)          │             │
│  └─────────┘                           │             │
└────────────────────────────────────────┼─────────────┘
                                         │ Encrypted
                                         │ Opaque Blobs
                                         ▼
                              ┌──────────────────────┐
                              │  Trustless Relay      │
                              │  Server               │
                              │                       │
                              │  • Room pub/sub       │
                              │  • Encrypted storage  │
                              │  • WebRTC signaling   │
                              │  • NEVER decrypts     │
                              └──────────────────────┘
```

