### 2. CRDT Engine (`src/core/`)

Custom CRDT implementations — no external CRDT library dependency. This keeps the framework lightweight, auditable, and tightly integrated with the encryption layer.

#### [NEW] [VectorClock.js](file:///home/privateproperty/Github/Ekya/src/core/VectorClock.js)
Causal ordering primitive. Methods: `increment(nodeId)`, `merge(other)`, `compare(other)` → `BEFORE | AFTER | CONCURRENT | EQUAL`. Used by all CRDTs to determine operation ordering.

#### [NEW] [GCounter.js](file:///home/privateproperty/Github/Ekya/src/core/GCounter.js)
Grow-only counter. Each node has its own count; value = sum of all counts. Methods: `increment()`, `merge(other)`, `value()`. Serializable state: `{ counts: { [nodeId]: number } }`.

#### [NEW] [LWWRegister.js](file:///home/privateproperty/Github/Ekya/src/core/LWWRegister.js)
Last-Writer-Wins Register. Stores a single value with a Hybrid Logical Clock timestamp. On conflict, highest timestamp wins. Methods: `set(value)`, `get()`, `merge(other)`.

#### [NEW] [LWWMap.js](file:///home/privateproperty/Github/Ekya/src/core/LWWMap.js)
Map composed of LWW-Registers. Each key maps to an `LWWRegister`. Supports `set(key, value)`, `get(key)`, `delete(key)` (tombstone), `merge(other)`, `toJSON()`. Ideal for structured documents / key-value state.

#### [NEW] [RGA.js](file:///home/privateproperty/Github/Ekya/src/core/RGA.js)
Replicated Growable Array — the core data structure for collaborative text editing. Operations: `insert(index, char, nodeId)`, `delete(index)`. Each element has a unique ID `(nodeId, sequence)`. Merging respects causal + total ordering. Methods: `insert()`, `delete()`, `merge(ops)`, `toString()`, `toArray()`.

#### [NEW] [Operation.js](file:///home/privateproperty/Github/Ekya/src/core/Operation.js)
Defines the `Operation` class: `{ type, crdtId, nodeId, clock, data }`. All CRDT mutations produce operations. Operations are what get encrypted and transmitted.

#### [NEW] [Serializer.js](file:///home/privateproperty/Github/Ekya/src/core/Serializer.js)
Uses `msgpackr` to serialize/deserialize operations and CRDT state to compact binary. Methods: `encode(obj) → Buffer`, `decode(buffer) → obj`.

