### 3. Encryption Layer (`src/crypto/`)

Following SecureConnect's patterns but adapted for CRDT operations. Using Web Crypto API (via Node.js `crypto.subtle`) for cross-environment compatibility.

#### [NEW] [KeyManager.js](file:///home/privateproperty/Github/Ekya/src/crypto/KeyManager.js)
Manages identity key pairs and document keys.
- `generateIdentityKeyPair()` — ECDH P-256 key pair (for key agreement)
- `deriveSharedSecret(myPrivateKey, theirPublicKey)` — ECDH shared secret
- `deriveDocumentKey(sharedSecret, documentId)` — HKDF-SHA256 to derive per-document AES-256-GCM key
- `exportPublicKey(key)` / `importPublicKey(raw)` — for key exchange
- `generateDocumentKey()` — random AES-256-GCM key for initial document creation

#### [NEW] [EncryptedEnvelope.js](file:///home/privateproperty/Github/Ekya/src/crypto/EncryptedEnvelope.js)
Wraps CRDT operations in encrypted envelopes.
- `encryptOperation(operation, documentKey)` → `{ iv, ciphertext, epoch, documentId }`
- `decryptOperation(envelope, documentKey)` → `Operation`
- `encryptSnapshot(crdtState, documentKey)` → `{ iv, ciphertext, epoch, documentId }`
- `decryptSnapshot(envelope, documentKey)` → CRDT state
- Uses AES-256-GCM with random 12-byte IV per encryption

#### [NEW] [KeyRotation.js](file:///home/privateproperty/Github/Ekya/src/crypto/KeyRotation.js)
Epoch-based key rotation.
- `rotateKey(currentEpoch)` — generates new document key, increments epoch
- `getKeyForEpoch(epoch)` — retrieves historical key (kept in memory/storage for decrypting old messages)
- Triggers snapshot creation on rotation so new members don't need old keys

---

### 4. Networking Layer (`src/net/`)

#### [NEW] [WebSocketTransport.js](file:///home/privateproperty/Github/Ekya/src/net/WebSocketTransport.js)
Client-side WebSocket transport. Connects to the relay server.
- `connect(url)`, `disconnect()`, `send(envelope)`, `onMessage(callback)`
- Handles reconnection with exponential backoff
- Emits events: `connected`, `disconnected`, `message`, `error`

#### [NEW] [WebRTCTransport.js](file:///home/privateproperty/Github/Ekya/src/net/WebRTCTransport.js)
Peer-to-peer transport using WebRTC data channels.
- `createPeer(signalingClient)`, `connect(peerId)`, `send(envelope)`, `onMessage(callback)`
- Uses the relay server only for signaling (ICE candidates, SDP exchange)
- Data channel configured for `reliable` ordered delivery

#### [NEW] [SignalingClient.js](file:///home/privateproperty/Github/Ekya/src/net/SignalingClient.js)
Handles WebRTC signaling through the relay server.
- `sendOffer(peerId, sdp)`, `sendAnswer(peerId, sdp)`, `sendCandidate(peerId, candidate)`
- `onOffer(callback)`, `onAnswer(callback)`, `onCandidate(callback)`

#### [NEW] [SyncProtocol.js](file:///home/privateproperty/Github/Ekya/src/net/SyncProtocol.js)
Manages synchronization of encrypted CRDT state.
- `broadcastOperation(encryptedOp)` — sends to all connected peers/server
- `requestSnapshot(documentId)` — asks server for latest encrypted snapshot
- `handleIncoming(envelope)` — decrypts, applies to local CRDT, triggers events
- Buffers operations during offline, flushes on reconnect

#### [NEW] [AwarenessProtocol.js](file:///home/privateproperty/Github/Ekya/src/net/AwarenessProtocol.js)
Presence and cursor awareness (NOT encrypted — intentionally public metadata).
- `setLocalState({ cursor, selection, user })` — broadcasts awareness info
- `onRemoteStateChange(callback)` — receives peer awareness updates
- Periodic heartbeat to detect disconnected peers (30s timeout)

---

### 5. Trustless Relay Server (`server/`)

The server is intentionally "dumb" — it **never sees plaintext**.

#### [NEW] [RelayServer.js](file:///home/privateproperty/Github/Ekya/server/RelayServer.js)
Main server entry point built with `ws` (WebSocket library).
- Room management: `createRoom(roomId)`, `joinRoom(roomId, clientId)`, `leaveRoom(roomId, clientId)`
- Message forwarding: receives encrypted envelopes, broadcasts to room members
- WebRTC signaling relay: forwards SDP offers/answers/ICE candidates between peers
- Encrypted snapshot storage: stores latest encrypted snapshot per room (in-memory + optional file persistence)
- No decryption keys, no knowledge of plaintext — pure relay

#### [NEW] [RoomManager.js](file:///home/privateproperty/Github/Ekya/server/RoomManager.js)
Manages room state: connected clients, room metadata (creation time, member count).

#### [NEW] [SnapshotStore.js](file:///home/privateproperty/Github/Ekya/server/SnapshotStore.js)
Persists encrypted snapshots. Interface: `save(roomId, encryptedSnapshot)`, `load(roomId)`. Default implementation: in-memory Map with optional JSON file backup.

