## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Custom CRDT Implementation vs. Library**: This plan builds CRDTs from scratch rather than wrapping Yjs/Automerge. This gives full control over the encryption integration (operations are encrypted at the source rather than wrapping an opaque library), keeps the dep tree minimal, and makes the codebase fully auditable. The trade-off is that these CRDTs are simpler than Yjs/Automerge (no rich-text formatting, no complex document trees). If you'd prefer to wrap Yjs instead, let me know.

> [!IMPORTANT]  
> **Encryption Algorithm Choice**: The plan uses ECDH P-256 + HKDF + AES-256-GCM (Web Crypto API). SecureConnect uses RSA-OAEP + AES-GCM. ECDH is chosen here because it produces smaller keys and enables efficient key agreement between peers. If you want RSA for consistency with SecureConnect, I can switch.

> [!NOTE]
> **Kalpa Integration**: The relay server is built standalone for now. A future enhancement could replace it with a Kalpa configuration that routes WebSocket ↔ WebRTC signaling using UME format, making the relay server a zero-code Kalpa YAML config.

